{
  "stem": "1061.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But I can assure you, even though I really don't know that for a fact, nobody ever could have expected what really came.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You know, people were still around who went through the first war, and there was plenty of horror in the first war.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And historically, Poland, even though it was freed in 1918, they still had a war with the Russians in 1920.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You see?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So that-- and then they, after almost 200 years of being enslaved, the Polish nation, so to say, had to bring itself up.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So things weren't really-- things were always in flux between the first war and the second war, in the interwar period.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But people from Lodz or wherever else they came from, who were shipped into our home town, probably took it as one aspect of this new war.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You know, what happened in the other war, they didn't have bombs.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, this war, they had bombs, you see.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The last war, whatever they had or didn't have, this was a little different.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So you sort of allowed yourself to account for it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Not myself, but I can imagine, you know, the shifts of population and such.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But nobody, I can assure you, would ever have thought that the final-- the final point in that progression would be the final solution, which is obliterating a whole nation.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that is the point.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So that I really don't think-- well, these people from Lodz ghetto, they came in 1941, you see, so there wasn't yet-- The real final solution that was signed, sealed, and delivered was in 1942 in the Wannsee-- at the Wannsee Conference.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So, you see, prior to that, you could still rationalize that this was just population shifting or whatever it was.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
